  "prompt": "What is commissioning?",
  "response": "Commissioning is a systematic process of ensuring that a building, system, or equipment is designed, installed, tested, operated, and maintained according to the owner's operational needs and design intent. It typically involves several key steps:\n\n1. Pre-design phase\n- Defining project goals and requirements\n- Establishing performance criteria\n\n2. Design phase\n- Reviewing design documents\n- Verifying design meets owner's requirements\n- Developing commissioning specifications\n\n3. Construction phase\n- Verifying equipment installation\n- Conducting functional performance testing\n- Documenting system performance\n- Training building operators\n\n4. Post-occupancy phase\n- Ongoing monitoring\n- Verification of system performance\n- Potential system adjustments\n\nCommissioning is commonly used in:\n- Building construction\n- HVAC systems\n- Mechanical and electrical systems\n- Industrial facilities\n- Healthcare facilities\n- Data centers\n\nTypes of commissioning include:\n- New construction commissioning\n- Existing building commissioning\n- Retro-commissioning\n- Re-commissioning\n\nThe primary goals are to:\n- Improve energy efficiency\n- Ensure system reliability\n- Optimize performance\n- Reduce operational costs\n- Enhance occupant comfort",
